Love has led me to a point
where I now live badly
’cause I’m dying of desire
I therefore can’t feel sorry for myself
and —
—Anonymous, 14th-century French Provençal

Malika is concerned with questions of language and the ways to communicate with the emergent singularity. From Uzbek family, she spends beginning of her career in St. Petersburg, working as a journalist and connecting this practice to her critical way of thinking and writing the code. When she learns about Cyberstan and people involved in the project, she instantly decides to go there and join the fighting forces.
